{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-0112"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Rice-Paddy Operations Coordination"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "0112"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :agriculture/rice-growing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:food-security :rural-employment :environmental-stewardship]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :paddy-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :audit-ledger]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:telemetry :optimization :dmn :bpmn]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "RiceOpsAdvisor ⊣ Paddy Operations Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph
 (langgraph.graph, riceops.operation/build), append-only audit ledger
 (riceops.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore and a DatomicStore
 backed by langchain.db via langchain-store.core). A back-office
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for rice-paddy field management
 (japonica/indica/glutinous/aromatic/upland) -- not direct
 field/irrigation-equipment operation authority and not
 pesticide-application-decision authority. Four ops
 (`:log-field-record` / `:schedule-field-operation` /
 `:flag-crop-health-concern` / `:order-supplies`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Six HARD invariants (field-not-registered,
 no-execution, equipment-or-pesticide-decision-blocked, op-not-allowed,
 field-record-invalid, water-level-invalid) plus independent
 cost/acreage/water-level/confidence verification (`riceops.registry`)
 elaborate this blueprint's Governor. Crop-health-concern flagging
 ALWAYS escalates to a human farmer/agronomist via the compiled
 graph's `:request-approval` node (`interrupt-before`,
 checkpoint-based resume); `:log-field-record` and
 `:schedule-field-operation` are the ops eligible to auto-commit, and
 only at phase 3 when the Governor is clean. Every commit/hold/
 approval-rejected decision lands in the append-only ledger, demo
 runnable end-to-end against both Store backends (`clojure
 -M:dev:run`); the GitHub Pages operator console
 (`docs/samples/operator-console.html`) is generated at build time by
 actually running the compiled StateGraph, including a genuine
 checkpoint resume for one resolved escalation
 (`clojure -M:dev:render-html`)."}
